Jonathan King (born Kenneth George King, 6 December 1944) is an English singer-songwriter, record producer, music entrepreneur, and former television and radio presenter.
He first came to prominence in 1965 when "Everyone's Gone to the Moon", a song that he wrote and sang while still an undergraduate, achieved chart success.
As an independent producer, he discovered and named the rock band Genesis in 1967, producing their first album From Genesis to Revelation.
He founded his own label UK Records in 1972.
He released and produced songs for 10cc and the Bay City Rollers.
